        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 400 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 9 miles south of Bronson to Topeka to Syracuse.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Auburn, Kendallville, Angola, Garrett, Ligonier, Lagrange, Avilla,
Albion, Waterloo, Fremont, Rome City, Topeka, Ray, Wolcottville,
Ashley, Hudson, Cromwell, Orland, Clear Lake, and Corunna.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 329 and 357.
Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 127 and 151.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
